title: Sead Ramović
text:
Sead Ramović (born 14 March 1979 in <a href="Stuttgart">Stuttgart</a>, <a href="West%20Germany">West Germany</a>) is a German football manager and retired <a href="Association%20football">football</a> <a href="Goalkeeper%20%28association%20football%29">goalkeeper</a>.  who is the manager of <a href="Qatar%20Stars%20League">PSL</a> team, <a href="TS%20Galaxy%20F.C.">TS Galaxy FC</a>.
Club career.
Ramović started his career with FC Feuerbach. Since then, he has played for SpVgg Feuerbach, <a href="Stuttgarter%20Kickers">Stuttgarter Kickers</a>, <a href="VfL%20Wolfsburg">VfL Wolfsburg</a>, <a href="Borussia%20M%C3%B6nchengladbach">Borussia Mönchengladbach</a>, and <a href="Kickers%20Offenbach">Kickers Offenbach</a>, all of which are <a href="Germany">German</a> clubs. In July 2006, he signed with the <a href="Norway">Norwegian</a> <a href="Norwegian%20Premier%20League">Tippeligaen</a> club <a href="Troms%C3%B8%20IL">Tromsø IL</a>. In 2010, he signed for <a href="Sivasspor">Sivasspor</a>. In 2011, he moved to <a href="FK%20Novi%20Pazar">FK Novi Pazar</a> and played in the <a href="Serbian%20Superliga">Serbian Superliga</a>. On 17 November 2011, it was announced that he is to join <a href="Lillestr%C3%B8m%20SK">Lillestrøm SK</a> for the 2012 season.
Following limited use with <a href="Vendsyssel%20FF">Vendsyssel</a> in the 2013 season, Ramović joined <a href="Str%C3%B8msgodset%20IF">Strømsgodset</a> before the 2014 season, but retired from the team early in the season, on 21 May.
International career.
Ramović received his first call up for the <a href="Bosnia%20and%20Herzegovina%20national%20football%20team">Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team</a> in 2004. Although he was included in the squad on several occasions, he never earned a cap.
